&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.kiva.org/image.php?type=thumbnail&amp;id=588859" align="left" alt="photo" title="Juan Carlos Castellon" border="1"/&gt;   &lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;$425 of $700 raised.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Started raising funds on Sep 1, 2010 &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Juan is a very hardworking man who is dedicated to his family of five children. He learned to repair household electrical goods and welding when he was young, and also buys and sells vehicles. With his savings he bought a vehicle that has been circulating. He buys and sells and gets a good profit.
He works hard in the electrical repair business, and when not doing that he welds to be able to buy his basic food, and he has the help of his wife who works as a domestic maid. And above all, the support of the loan institution through 12 loan cycles has enabled him to improve his home and build it from concrete.
With this loan, he will finish making the porch, put in a proper floor over the current earth floor, and improve the roof, which is in bad condition. For him, it is a pleasure every day to improve his family's well being, which working with Afodenic has made possible. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translated from Spanish by Alison Hynd, Kiva Volunteer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;br clear="all"&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.kiva.org/image.php?type=thumbnail&amp;id=591157" align="left" alt="photo" title="Wiliam Fernando Martinez Cortez" border="1"/&gt;   &lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;$300 of $375 raised.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Started raising funds on Sep 1, 2010 &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Sr. William is a hardworking gentleman and the father of two children who are in school. He has worked as a driver for several years and does not earn very much on his fixed salary, so he makes whatever adjustments are necessary in order to meet his daily needs.
&lt;p&gt;
With the support of AFODENIC, he has been able to make improvements to his home through seven loan cycles. William has been able to put up concrete walls, install room dividers, and lay down a floor in his living room. Now he wants to build a small wall in front of his home to replace the sheets of tin that line his property. He wants to make this improvement in order to provide safer and cleaner conditions.
&lt;p&gt;
The loan will be used to buy the necessary materials such as stone, sand, cement, and iron so that the work can begin. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translated from Spanish by Ronan Reodica, Kiva Volunteer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;br clear="all"&gt;
